HEADWORD: coralwood
<hw>coralwood</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an East Indian tree
(<spn>Adenanthera pavonina</spn>) with racemes of yellow-white flowers;
cultivated as an ornamental.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> red sandalwood, Barbados pride, peacock flower
fence, <spn>Adenanthera pavonina</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
